version_description: The Chords at the Beginnig of the row of Verse 1-3 are played on beat 1 and the vocal beginns at beat 1 and(1,5). The Chords standing after vowels on a consonant mostly are meant to be played at the end of the vowel. The chords are played broken in the Verses in the original, I recommend to use an guitar- or piano-sound (or instrument of course) for the Verses and an organ-sound for the refrain. At the refrain there are the Organ-Chords I heard, the other instruments are playing lines which are making the great effect of the song. The Low line at the Chorus is: D2,C2,B1,G1, C2,B1,A1,G1, F#1, F1, B1, E2(1 chord per block, transposed down individually because it sounds different addicted to what instrument you are using). I Hope you enjoy my version of this great Track.
Added actual chorus after each verse.
